'''Gollum browser''' is a [[web application]] designed to browse [[Wikipedia]] in an easier way than directly using the [[web browser]]. [[hyperlink|Link]]s external to Wikipedia are opened in the user's regular browser. Gollum is opened from a regular browser and makes a window that puts the Wikipedia search bar on the toolbar.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wayner|first=Peter|title=Top 10 specialty Web browsers you may have missed|url=http://www.infoworld.com/d/applications/top-10-specialty-web-browsers-you-may-have-missed-026?page=0,7|publisher=[[InfoWorld]]|accessdate=28 October 2010|page=7|date=19 October 2010}}</ref> Gollum was created by [[Harald Hanek]] in 2005 using [[PHP]] and [[Ajax (programming)|Ajax]].

According to one blogger, Gollum provides a way for Chinese users to access the English language of Wikipedia when the [[Blocking of Wikipedia by the People's Republic of China|Chinese government blocks wikipedia.org]].<ref>[http://www.danwei.org/internet/the_nanny_changes_her_mind_wik.php The Nanny changes her mind: Wikipedia blocked again]</ref>

==Languages==
Though the website is available only in English and German, Gollum's GUI is available in more than 32 languages<ref>http://gollum.easycp.de/en/0,1,00.html</ref> and can browse nearly 50 Wikipedia editions.

